===========
Quick Start
===========


Supported Versions
==================

Add-on developed and tested with Blender versions 4.2+ in mind.


.. _installation:

Installation
============

Available on `Blender Extensions <https://extensions.blender.org/add-ons/paws-bakery>`_
and `GitHub Releases <https://github.com/pawsgineer/b3d_paws_bakery/releases>`_

Usage
=====

The add-on automates material setup for baking and allow to run batched baking.
For better understanding of what you can achieve, I recommend to get familiar with
vanila Blender baking process.

Most of the add-on controls located in N-panel named `🍰PAWSBKR`.

-----
Modes
-----

Simple
------

Simple mode allows you bake currently selected objects to a single image.

.. image:: ../images/ui_simple_mode.png
   :align: center
   :class: no-scaled-link

Available `Bake Settings`_.

Texture Set
------

Texture Set mode allows you to specify list of objects and texture types to bake.

**Output Mode**

:Single Texture: Bake all the objects to a single atlas texture
:Per-Object: Create a separate image for every object in the list

Create Materials: Described in `Automatic Material Creation`_

.. image:: ../images/ui_texture_set_mode.png
   :align: center
   :class: no-scaled-link

Available `Bake Settings`_.


